WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.809 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:10.177 --> 00:00:10.878 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Hello, [inaudible].

00:00:10.878 --> 00:00:13.747 align:middle line:90%
Lilou here for Gaiam TV.

00:00:13.747 --> 00:00:17.551 align:middle line:84%
I'm in San Diego with John Gray,
that you probably recognize

00:00:17.551 --> 00:00:21.288 align:middle line:84%
because he wrote this awesome
book called, "Men Are From Mars,

00:00:21.288 --> 00:00:22.656 align:middle line:90%
Women Are From Venus."

00:00:22.656 --> 00:00:25.993 align:middle line:84%
And this totally shifted the
life of millions of people's,

00:00:25.993 --> 00:00:27.394 align:middle line:90%
you know, relationship.

00:00:27.394 --> 00:00:31.931 align:middle line:84%
Just really you brought a whole
new perspective on what --

00:00:31.931 --> 00:00:34.568 align:middle line:84%
how to create this
juicy relationship

00:00:34.568 --> 00:00:35.903 align:middle line:90%
that actually works.

00:00:35.903 --> 00:00:38.706 align:middle line:84%
So thank you for that; and I
know you came up with many,

00:00:38.706 --> 00:00:40.908 align:middle line:84%
many books and you sold
millions of copies,

00:00:40.908 --> 00:00:43.144 align:middle line:90%
and your latest one is --

00:00:43.144 --> 00:00:44.211 align:middle line:90%
>> John Gray: "Work With Me."

00:00:44.211 --> 00:00:45.546 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: -- "Work With Me."

00:00:45.546 --> 00:00:47.581 align:middle line:84%
>> John Gray: What's happened
today is since I wrote,

00:00:47.581 --> 00:00:49.383 align:middle line:84%
"Men Are From Mars,"
men are still men

00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:50.918 align:middle line:90%
and women are still women,

00:00:50.918 --> 00:00:52.987 align:middle line:84%
but the work world has
dramatically changed.

00:00:52.987 --> 00:00:55.456 align:middle line:84%
It's now the community
that women live in.

00:00:55.456 --> 00:00:57.525 align:middle line:84%
And it was a community
that was designed --

00:00:57.525 --> 00:01:00.728 align:middle line:84%
the rules of the workplace
are designed by men for men.

00:01:00.728 --> 00:01:03.296 align:middle line:84%
They're not really
intentionally against women,

00:01:03.296 --> 00:01:04.597 align:middle line:90%
but women don't feel supported.

00:01:04.597 --> 00:01:08.068 align:middle line:84%
And most people don't know
that your average woman

00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:11.372 align:middle line:84%
in the workplace has stress
levels which are measurable,

00:01:11.372 --> 00:01:13.274 align:middle line:90%
cortisol, the stress hormone,

00:01:13.274 --> 00:01:15.576 align:middle line:84%
twice as high as
the average male.

00:01:15.576 --> 00:01:17.778 align:middle line:84%
And when she returns
home, she's trying

00:01:17.778 --> 00:01:20.748 align:middle line:84%
to balance work outside
the home and work at home,

00:01:20.748 --> 00:01:23.751 align:middle line:84%
her stress levels are 4
times higher than a man.

00:01:23.751 --> 00:01:25.653 align:middle line:84%
Men don't know that,
women don't know that;

00:01:25.653 --> 00:01:27.254 align:middle line:90%
women experience that.

00:01:27.254 --> 00:01:31.025 align:middle line:84%
And what it means is that we
have to increase our awareness

00:01:31.025 --> 00:01:33.093 align:middle line:84%
of what are women
needing in the workplace,

00:01:33.093 --> 00:01:35.763 align:middle line:84%
and expand the culture
of the workplace

00:01:35.763 --> 00:01:39.567 align:middle line:84%
to not only support men,
but also to support women.

00:01:39.567 --> 00:01:42.770 align:middle line:84%
And the foundation of that
is not like everybody change,

00:01:42.770 --> 00:01:45.739 align:middle line:84%
it's actually just growing in
our awareness of our differences

00:01:45.739 --> 00:01:49.043 align:middle line:84%
and understanding them
in a positive way.

00:01:49.043 --> 00:01:52.580 align:middle line:84%
Understanding them then
allows us to feel compassion.

00:01:52.580 --> 00:01:55.449 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is
when people become aware

00:01:55.449 --> 00:01:56.849 align:middle line:90%
of this in our workshops.

00:01:56.849 --> 00:01:59.386 align:middle line:90%
Men feel much greater compassion

00:01:59.386 --> 00:02:00.621 align:middle line:84%
for what women are
going through.

00:02:00.621 --> 00:02:03.524 align:middle line:84%
And then their appreciation
of women goes up.

00:02:03.524 --> 00:02:06.694 align:middle line:84%
Women experience a greater
appreciation of men.

00:02:06.694 --> 00:02:10.129 align:middle line:84%
That's the first thing, because
so many women assume that much

00:02:10.129 --> 00:02:12.900 align:middle line:84%
of the mistreatment, quote,
"mistreatment" by men,

00:02:12.900 --> 00:02:15.002 align:middle line:84%
like they feel excluded,
they feel left out,

00:02:15.002 --> 00:02:17.771 align:middle line:84%
they feel unappreciated,
they feel unsupported,

00:02:17.771 --> 00:02:19.773 align:middle line:84%
they assume that
that's intentional.

00:02:19.773 --> 00:02:22.610 align:middle line:84%
And most of it is that mean are
just oblivious, they really are.

00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:27.381 align:middle line:84%
And it's a culture that doesn't
promote in a sense the hormones

00:02:27.381 --> 00:02:29.216 align:middle line:84%
in a woman that will
lower her stress.

00:02:29.216 --> 00:02:31.518 align:middle line:84%
The culture promotes
the hormones

00:02:31.518 --> 00:02:33.254 align:middle line:90%
that will lower stress in men.

00:02:33.254 --> 00:02:34.555 align:middle line:90%
>> L: Yes.

00:02:34.555 --> 00:02:36.924 align:middle line:84%
But I guess we've heard a
lot that it starts from us.

00:02:36.924 --> 00:02:42.263 align:middle line:84%
So, for example, as women
what can we do to shift that

00:02:42.263 --> 00:02:46.100 align:middle line:84%
and to be our delicious
self even at work?

00:02:46.100 --> 00:02:49.270 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: Exactly; so understanding
a woman's physiology

00:02:49.270 --> 00:02:52.606 align:middle line:84%
from a woman's point of view can
help her, as well as help men

00:02:52.606 --> 00:02:55.709 align:middle line:84%
to help their wives, and men
to understand themselves,

00:02:55.709 --> 00:02:57.111 align:middle line:90%
and also for our children.

00:02:57.111 --> 00:03:01.682 align:middle line:84%
So the new research reveals that
cortisol, the stress hormone,

00:03:01.682 --> 00:03:06.053 align:middle line:84%
if you're a woman, the hormone
oxytocin is what lowers her

00:03:06.053 --> 00:03:07.454 align:middle line:90%
stress hormone.

00:03:07.454 --> 00:03:10.591 align:middle line:84%
So, for example, if a woman's
in a yoga class, and she's not

00:03:10.591 --> 00:03:13.060 align:middle line:84%
in a hurry, and she's with a
whole bunch of other women,

00:03:13.060 --> 00:03:17.264 align:middle line:84%
and they're all in synchrony,
she doesn't feel alone,

00:03:17.264 --> 00:03:19.366 align:middle line:90%
her oxytocin levels go up.

00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:22.970 align:middle line:84%
If a woman's getting her hair
done, and somebody's massaging

00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:26.974 align:middle line:84%
and washing her head, it's
a major oxytocin producer.

00:03:26.974 --> 00:03:29.143 align:middle line:84%
You know, because I get
my hair done and he wants

00:03:29.143 --> 00:03:31.545 align:middle line:84%
to wash my hair I go, "Why;
I shampooed this morning.

00:03:31.545 --> 00:03:32.746 align:middle line:90%
What's the big deal?"

00:03:32.746 --> 00:03:35.716 align:middle line:84%
[Laughs] But women
have a greater benefit.

00:03:35.716 --> 00:03:38.952 align:middle line:84%
Shopping, for example; when
women feel they have plenty

00:03:38.952 --> 00:03:42.189 align:middle line:84%
of time, most women who enjoy
shopping if they have time

00:03:42.189 --> 00:03:45.459 align:middle line:84%
to enjoy it, it raises
their oxytocin levels.

00:03:45.459 --> 00:03:49.263 align:middle line:84%
Dressing; how does she look,
how will she appear to others?

00:03:49.263 --> 00:03:51.699 align:middle line:84%
When she's able to
express her beauty,

00:03:51.699 --> 00:03:54.401 align:middle line:90%
that is an oxytocin rebuilder.

00:03:54.401 --> 00:03:58.072 align:middle line:84%
Makeup; when a woman is able
to put a little makeup on,

00:03:58.072 --> 00:04:00.040 align:middle line:84%
or a good skin cream, or
whatever it is so that

00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:04.611 align:middle line:84%
when she looks in the mirror she
sees her healthy self, vibrant,

00:04:04.611 --> 00:04:08.415 align:middle line:84%
and what happens is when you see
beauty it inspires beauty inside

00:04:08.415 --> 00:04:11.151 align:middle line:84%
of you, and when you feel
beautiful, like we're surrounded

00:04:11.151 --> 00:04:14.421 align:middle line:84%
in beautiful nature here,
it awakens that inside.

00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:16.889 align:middle line:84%
And that is an oxytocin
producer.

00:04:16.889 --> 00:04:20.026 align:middle line:84%
So this is like to become
aware for women of the things

00:04:20.026 --> 00:04:21.060 align:middle line:90%
that help them to cope

00:04:21.060 --> 00:04:23.364 align:middle line:84%
with stress is very,
very significant.

00:04:23.364 --> 00:04:24.832 align:middle line:84%
>> L: I hear that
then it's important

00:04:24.832 --> 00:04:26.967 align:middle line:90%
to cultivate the feminine side,

00:04:26.967 --> 00:04:29.503 align:middle line:84%
because we became
very masculine, huh?

00:04:29.503 --> 00:04:31.538 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: Well, that's what I
talk about in "Work With Me,"

00:04:31.538 --> 00:04:35.476 align:middle line:84%
the new book, which is my
coauthor, Barbara Annis,

00:04:35.476 --> 00:04:37.144 align:middle line:84%
who's been working in
the corporate world

00:04:37.144 --> 00:04:39.046 align:middle line:84%
and now teaches gender
intelligence

00:04:39.046 --> 00:04:41.849 align:middle line:84%
in the corporate world, which
is what we teach together now.

00:04:41.849 --> 00:04:45.419 align:middle line:84%
And she was what she calls
herself, "the third sex,"

00:04:45.419 --> 00:04:47.888 align:middle line:84%
meaning she's a woman,
but she became a man

00:04:47.888 --> 00:04:49.456 align:middle line:84%
to be successful
in the workplace.

00:04:49.456 --> 00:04:53.427 align:middle line:84%
And she saw that she was burning
out, and many of her other women

00:04:53.427 --> 00:04:55.396 align:middle line:84%
in that situation
were burning out.

00:04:55.396 --> 00:04:57.331 align:middle line:84%
We now have the actual
research showing

00:04:57.331 --> 00:05:00.167 align:middle line:84%
that women's stress
levels shoot up much higher

00:05:00.167 --> 00:05:01.502 align:middle line:90%
when they're in the workplace.

00:05:01.502 --> 00:05:04.271 align:middle line:84%
Why is that; because it's
the workplace that's designed

00:05:04.271 --> 00:05:07.441 align:middle line:84%
to support men, not
against women.

00:05:07.441 --> 00:05:08.876 align:middle line:84%
We have to remember
that; and that's part

00:05:08.876 --> 00:05:10.811 align:middle line:84%
of what would help women
experience less stress

00:05:10.811 --> 00:05:13.614 align:middle line:84%
in the workplace, at least to
feel like it's not intentionally

00:05:13.614 --> 00:05:15.716 align:middle line:90%
against her, but to recognize

00:05:15.716 --> 00:05:19.420 align:middle line:84%
that whenever you're
making a sacrifice for money

00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:21.789 align:middle line:84%
for a man it releases
testosterone

00:05:21.789 --> 00:05:23.424 align:middle line:90%
and lowers his stress.

00:05:23.424 --> 00:05:26.794 align:middle line:84%
When a woman makes a sacrifice
for money, she gets money

00:05:26.794 --> 00:05:30.097 align:middle line:84%
to pay bills at home, but
it doesn't lower her stress.

00:05:30.097 --> 00:05:33.734 align:middle line:84%
Whenever you make a sacrifice,
it releases testosterone.

00:05:33.734 --> 00:05:36.770 align:middle line:84%
Whenever you're in an emergency
job, or an urgency job,

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:40.307 align:middle line:84%
or a deadline, or you make
the client more important

00:05:40.307 --> 00:05:41.642 align:middle line:90%
than yourself.

00:05:41.642 --> 00:05:42.876 align:middle line:84%
And that's really the rules
of the workplace, you know,

00:05:42.876 --> 00:05:46.246 align:middle line:84%
client first, yes is
always the answer.

00:05:46.246 --> 00:05:47.314 align:middle line:90%
You're not allowed to say,

00:05:47.314 --> 00:05:49.616 align:middle line:84%
"What is personally
fulfilling for me?"

00:05:49.616 --> 00:05:51.585 align:middle line:84%
But that's one of the
female values that comes

00:05:51.585 --> 00:05:54.755 align:middle line:84%
into the workplace as we begin
to hear this from women more.

00:05:54.755 --> 00:05:57.090 align:middle line:84%
In a sense, men are not
allowed to complain.

00:05:57.090 --> 00:06:00.828 align:middle line:84%
You're a wimp, you're a
whiner if you complain,

00:06:00.828 --> 00:06:02.062 align:middle line:90%
as opposed to say, "Hey,

00:06:02.062 --> 00:06:04.498 align:middle line:84%
we could improve the
conditions of the workplace."

00:06:04.498 --> 00:06:06.300 align:middle line:84%
As women have come
into the workplace,

00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:08.202 align:middle line:84%
conditions are dramatically
improving,

00:06:08.202 --> 00:06:10.504 align:middle line:90%
not just for women, but for men.

00:06:10.504 --> 00:06:14.174 align:middle line:84%
And the acceleration of this
process can be dramatically

00:06:14.174 --> 00:06:17.578 align:middle line:84%
increased in a positive way
with greater understanding

00:06:17.578 --> 00:06:19.746 align:middle line:84%
of those differences
in a positive way.

00:06:19.746 --> 00:06:23.016 align:middle line:84%
That's what we call "gender
intelligence," the intelligence

00:06:23.016 --> 00:06:24.918 align:middle line:84%
to be able to take
diversity, and particularly one

00:06:24.918 --> 00:06:27.721 align:middle line:84%
of the biggest diversities
is between men and women,

00:06:27.721 --> 00:06:29.523 align:middle line:90%
and unite those worlds.

00:06:29.523 --> 00:06:32.493 align:middle line:84%
So we found with 8 blind
spots -- and this is --

00:06:32.493 --> 00:06:34.561 align:middle line:84%
actually they all relate
to home, but we found it

00:06:34.561 --> 00:06:37.664 align:middle line:84%
in our survey of 250,000
people in the workplace

00:06:37.664 --> 00:06:40.100 align:middle line:90%
in 60 Fortune 500 companies.

00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:44.204 align:middle line:84%
We go in and we take a survey
before they take the workshop.

00:06:44.204 --> 00:06:45.839 align:middle line:90%
Oh my gosh, men are blown away.

00:06:45.839 --> 00:06:47.407 align:middle line:90%
They just go, "I didn't know."

00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:48.575 align:middle line:84%
You see, there are
so many things

00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:50.811 align:middle line:84%
that we don't know
that we don't know.

00:06:50.811 --> 00:06:51.912 align:middle line:90%
>> L: Yes, yes.

00:06:51.912 --> 00:06:52.913 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: And when that's
pointed out to you,

00:06:52.913 --> 00:06:54.248 align:middle line:90%
you go, "I just didn't know."

00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:55.983 align:middle line:84%
It's like say there's a
door that you can walk

00:06:55.983 --> 00:06:58.819 align:middle line:84%
through the wall right here,
but I don't know what's there,

00:06:58.819 --> 00:07:00.287 align:middle line:90%
I'll always go the long route.

00:07:00.287 --> 00:07:03.023 align:middle line:84%
And somebody says, "You know,
there's a door right here."

00:07:03.023 --> 00:07:04.424 align:middle line:90%
"I didn't know."

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:08.395 align:middle line:84%
It's an easy adaptation when you
raise understanding and insight.

00:07:08.395 --> 00:07:13.200 align:middle line:84%
So here's an example, 1 of the 8
"blind spots," we call them is,

00:07:13.200 --> 00:07:15.402 align:middle line:90%
"Are women feeling excluded?"

00:07:15.402 --> 00:07:18.038 align:middle line:90%
If you ask men in corporations,

00:07:18.038 --> 00:07:20.007 align:middle line:84%
"Do you exclude the
women you work with?"

00:07:20.007 --> 00:07:21.408 align:middle line:90%
"No. I think they're wonderful.

00:07:21.408 --> 00:07:23.010 align:middle line:90%
They have equal opportunity."

00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:26.046 align:middle line:84%
Ask the women, and
over 60% of women feel,

00:07:26.046 --> 00:07:28.715 align:middle line:84%
personally feel,
"I'm being excluded."

00:07:28.715 --> 00:07:29.850 align:middle line:84%
>> L: "I'm not in
the boys' club."

00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:30.684 align:middle line:90%
>> JG: That's exactly it.

00:07:30.684 --> 00:07:31.952 align:middle line:90%
That's one of the aspects.

00:07:31.952 --> 00:07:33.320 align:middle line:90%
And so you take it personally.

00:07:33.320 --> 00:07:34.788 align:middle line:84%
You feel like you're
pushing against them.

00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:36.156 align:middle line:90%
It's a fight.

00:07:36.156 --> 00:07:38.625 align:middle line:84%
And granted, 30 years ago it
was a fight for women to prove

00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:40.627 align:middle line:84%
that they can do
everything a man can do,

00:07:40.627 --> 00:07:42.563 align:middle line:90%
but they had to do it like men.

00:07:42.563 --> 00:07:45.565 align:middle line:84%
We're trying to bring in as
an awareness of the strengths,

00:07:45.565 --> 00:07:48.569 align:middle line:84%
not just that the differences
are positive, but the strengths

00:07:48.569 --> 00:07:51.438 align:middle line:84%
that women have are amazing
to bring into the workplace.

00:07:51.438 --> 00:07:53.440 align:middle line:90%
So here's a little takeaway.

00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:57.077 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting at a table with
my team, 3 men, 3 women.

00:07:57.077 --> 00:08:00.547 align:middle line:84%
We're discussing something,
our plans, we meet every week.

00:08:00.547 --> 00:08:03.850 align:middle line:84%
And in that meeting 2
women might not be talking.

00:08:03.850 --> 00:08:06.587 align:middle line:84%
Most men will assume,
"If she's not talking,

00:08:06.587 --> 00:08:08.322 align:middle line:90%
she has nothing to say."

00:08:08.322 --> 00:08:10.257 align:middle line:84%
But often women are
waiting to be invited

00:08:10.257 --> 00:08:11.658 align:middle line:90%
into the conversation.

00:08:11.658 --> 00:08:14.962 align:middle line:84%
It may be happening at a speed
that is not inclusive to her;

00:08:14.962 --> 00:08:17.931 align:middle line:84%
because you have to
realize, well all men have

00:08:17.931 --> 00:08:21.068 align:middle line:84%
at least 30 times more
testosterone than women.

00:08:21.068 --> 00:08:24.304 align:middle line:84%
And testosterone allows you to
jump in there and react fast.

00:08:24.304 --> 00:08:27.774 align:middle line:84%
That's what testosterone is,
it's a flight or fight response

00:08:27.774 --> 00:08:31.044 align:middle line:84%
for men is to run fast,
act fast, to think fast,

00:08:31.044 --> 00:08:33.380 align:middle line:84%
often without thinking
to say something.

00:08:33.380 --> 00:08:35.648 align:middle line:84%
So women are -- sometimes women
are like trying to take all this

00:08:35.648 --> 00:08:37.351 align:middle line:84%
in because they're
good listeners,

00:08:37.351 --> 00:08:39.419 align:middle line:84%
and it's like there's
no room for her to come

00:08:39.419 --> 00:08:40.820 align:middle line:90%
into the conversation.

00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:43.290 align:middle line:84%
So when the men hear this, and
they hear all the women saying

00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:44.458 align:middle line:90%
that they say, "Well, I thought

00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:46.426 align:middle line:84%
that you always had
opportunity to speak up."

00:08:46.426 --> 00:08:48.428 align:middle line:84%
And with that awareness
I'm able to notice

00:08:48.428 --> 00:08:51.131 align:middle line:84%
when women aren't talking I
don't assume they have nothing

00:08:51.131 --> 00:08:52.398 align:middle line:90%
to say.

00:08:52.398 --> 00:08:54.434 align:middle line:84%
I assume they're thinking
deeply, and I'll say like,

00:08:54.434 --> 00:08:56.937 align:middle line:84%
"Marci, you've had a lot
of experience with this.

00:08:56.937 --> 00:08:58.405 align:middle line:90%
What do you think?"

00:08:58.405 --> 00:09:00.307 align:middle line:90%
And then she had so much to say.

00:09:00.307 --> 00:09:03.310 align:middle line:84%
There's always so much more that
women want to add to the table

00:09:03.310 --> 00:09:07.147 align:middle line:84%
that often doesn't come out
because women feel excluded.

00:09:07.147 --> 00:09:08.181 align:middle line:90%
>> L: We don't communicate

00:09:08.181 --> 00:09:11.251 align:middle line:84%
at all the same way
in the workplace.

00:09:11.251 --> 00:09:13.120 align:middle line:84%
Like it seems like
we just don't have --

00:09:13.120 --> 00:09:15.789 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't come out the same
way, and then men don't even --

00:09:15.789 --> 00:09:17.190 align:middle line:90%
maybe even understand us.

00:09:17.190 --> 00:09:18.992 align:middle line:90%
So we even withdraw.

00:09:18.992 --> 00:09:20.127 align:middle line:90%
>> JG: Well, there's 2 aspects

00:09:20.127 --> 00:09:22.996 align:middle line:84%
to how men misunderstand
women in that example.

00:09:22.996 --> 00:09:25.432 align:middle line:84%
One is that women often
see a bigger picture.

00:09:25.432 --> 00:09:27.467 align:middle line:84%
They're going to take
into more considerations,

00:09:27.467 --> 00:09:29.903 align:middle line:84%
whereas men are kind of like
refocused on, "How do we get

00:09:29.903 --> 00:09:31.505 align:middle line:90%
from point A to point B?"

00:09:31.505 --> 00:09:34.107 align:middle line:84%
Women might point out, "Well,
how would that affect others?

00:09:34.107 --> 00:09:37.077 align:middle line:84%
How does that affect
farther into the future?

00:09:37.077 --> 00:09:39.012 align:middle line:84%
How does that relate
to more in the past?

00:09:39.012 --> 00:09:40.213 align:middle line:90%
What have we seen?"

00:09:40.213 --> 00:09:41.882 align:middle line:84%
So she's going to
have a bigger picture.

00:09:41.882 --> 00:09:45.085 align:middle line:84%
And often men think,
"She's slowing us down."

00:09:45.085 --> 00:09:47.454 align:middle line:84%
You know, there's a great
commercial for a phone company

00:09:47.454 --> 00:09:50.090 align:middle line:84%
with a bunch of children
in a kindergarten class,

00:09:50.090 --> 00:09:52.793 align:middle line:84%
and the man's saying, "Which
is better, fast or slow?"

00:09:52.793 --> 00:09:55.195 align:middle line:84%
And they're all saying,
"Fast, fast, fast."

00:09:55.195 --> 00:09:58.365 align:middle line:84%
Well, fast is good sometimes,
and slow is good sometimes.

00:09:58.365 --> 00:10:01.234 align:middle line:84%
And often women will bring
up more considerations

00:10:01.234 --> 00:10:04.504 align:middle line:84%
and men will often think, "Well,
she's just slowing us down."

00:10:04.504 --> 00:10:06.506 align:middle line:84%
But if we could actually
see that that's a virtue

00:10:06.506 --> 00:10:09.109 align:middle line:84%
and a value, and if
women don't exploit that,

00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:11.078 align:middle line:84%
because sometimes businesses
will have a committee

00:10:11.078 --> 00:10:12.779 align:middle line:90%
that goes on talking forever.

00:10:12.779 --> 00:10:15.682 align:middle line:84%
So often women when I explore it
more through verbal conversation

00:10:15.682 --> 00:10:18.685 align:middle line:84%
of the possibilities and
opportunities and so forth,

00:10:18.685 --> 00:10:21.154 align:middle line:84%
they're also very
wise in enlisting --

00:10:21.154 --> 00:10:23.356 align:middle line:90%
creating a sense of inclusion,

00:10:23.356 --> 00:10:26.193 align:middle line:84%
because to truly motivate people
you want to include people

00:10:26.193 --> 00:10:27.961 align:middle line:84%
and then they become
more motivated.

00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:31.031 align:middle line:84%
So that's one aspect
of the differences.

00:10:31.031 --> 00:10:34.534 align:middle line:84%
One of the blind spots we saw
was another question, which is,

00:10:34.534 --> 00:10:37.104 align:middle line:84%
"Are women too emotional
in the workplace?"

00:10:37.104 --> 00:10:39.606 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, most
women said, "No."

00:10:39.606 --> 00:10:41.408 align:middle line:90%
And most men said, "Yes,"

00:10:41.408 --> 00:10:43.376 align:middle line:84%
and they just don't
know what to do with it.

00:10:43.376 --> 00:10:45.812 align:middle line:84%
And we asked another question,
which is, "Do men walk

00:10:45.812 --> 00:10:47.280 align:middle line:90%
on eggshells in the workplace?"

00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:50.217 align:middle line:84%
And women said, "Yes," and
men said, "Yes," [laughs]

00:10:50.217 --> 00:10:51.618 align:middle line:90%
when they're dealing with women.

00:10:51.618 --> 00:10:54.521 align:middle line:84%
And part of it is not
understanding how women cope

00:10:54.521 --> 00:10:58.023 align:middle line:84%
with stress quite commonly,
or men cope with stress.

00:10:58.023 --> 00:11:00.460 align:middle line:84%
In the back of the brain there's
the fight or flight center.

00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:02.896 align:middle line:84%
When we're under stress,
blood flows there.

00:11:02.896 --> 00:11:06.133 align:middle line:84%
And for a man it then goes to
the action part of the brain.

00:11:06.133 --> 00:11:09.236 align:middle line:84%
So a man wants to either do
something or think about it.

00:11:09.236 --> 00:11:11.138 align:middle line:84%
He detaches -- the
first reaction is

00:11:11.138 --> 00:11:13.573 align:middle line:90%
to detach from emotions.

00:11:13.573 --> 00:11:18.078 align:middle line:84%
For a woman the first reaction
is to connect with her emotions.

00:11:18.078 --> 00:11:20.247 align:middle line:84%
So women will have an
emotional response,

00:11:20.247 --> 00:11:24.651 align:middle line:84%
which men don't realize is just
a little wave, and it passes.

00:11:24.651 --> 00:11:27.554 align:middle line:84%
But for a minute she might
tear up, she might have a sense

00:11:27.554 --> 00:11:30.457 align:middle line:84%
of urgency, of fear in her
voice, or she have a sense

00:11:30.457 --> 00:11:32.025 align:middle line:90%
of frustration in her voice.

00:11:32.025 --> 00:11:33.827 align:middle line:84%
And a man goes, "Well, you
shouldn't feel that way.

00:11:33.827 --> 00:11:35.762 align:middle line:84%
You're making a big
deal out of nothing."

00:11:35.762 --> 00:11:37.964 align:middle line:84%
And she's not making
a big deal out of it.

00:11:37.964 --> 00:11:40.567 align:middle line:84%
The man is misinterpreting
her reaction

00:11:40.567 --> 00:11:42.736 align:middle line:90%
as if she's making a big deal.

00:11:42.736 --> 00:11:45.572 align:middle line:84%
And this is also in our
personal relationships as well.

00:11:45.572 --> 00:11:48.341 align:middle line:84%
All these things do bleed over
to the personal relationship.

00:11:48.341 --> 00:11:50.177 align:middle line:84%
So often men will
tell their wives,

00:11:50.177 --> 00:11:51.611 align:middle line:90%
you know, "It's not a big deal.

00:11:51.611 --> 00:11:52.579 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry about it.

00:11:52.579 --> 00:11:53.814 align:middle line:90%
It's not a problem.

00:11:53.814 --> 00:11:55.949 align:middle line:84%
I'll take care of it,
dear," that kind of a thing.

00:11:55.949 --> 00:11:58.018 align:middle line:84%
And she's not saying,
"I can't handle it."

00:11:58.018 --> 00:11:59.820 align:middle line:84%
See, the women in the workplace
might have an emotional

00:11:59.820 --> 00:12:02.222 align:middle line:84%
reaction, but that emotional
reaction doesn't mean,

00:12:02.222 --> 00:12:03.590 align:middle line:90%
"I can't handle it."

00:12:03.590 --> 00:12:06.626 align:middle line:84%
But men interpret it that
way for a simple reason.

00:12:06.626 --> 00:12:08.528 align:middle line:90%
Men's brains are different.

00:12:08.528 --> 00:12:11.998 align:middle line:84%
And men's brains they
only become emotional

00:12:11.998 --> 00:12:13.600 align:middle line:90%
when they can't handle it.

00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:16.570 align:middle line:84%
So for a man even if I'm chased
by -- if I'm in a tiger's cage,

00:12:16.570 --> 00:12:17.637 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to be emotional

00:12:17.637 --> 00:12:19.406 align:middle line:84%
because I have some
training with that.

00:12:19.406 --> 00:12:22.709 align:middle line:84%
But if I get emotional, it
means I'm out of control.

00:12:22.709 --> 00:12:25.946 align:middle line:84%
So men in a sense are
designed only to get emotional

00:12:25.946 --> 00:12:29.416 align:middle line:84%
if their problem is huge,
like a lion, a tiger, a bear,

00:12:29.416 --> 00:12:31.518 align:middle line:84%
and suddenly we feel
out of control,

00:12:31.518 --> 00:12:33.820 align:middle line:84%
then we get emotional
and we feel fear.

00:12:33.820 --> 00:12:35.622 align:middle line:84%
So fear comes up,
strong emotion.

00:12:35.622 --> 00:12:38.992 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, men don't have those
feelings generally speaking,

00:12:38.992 --> 00:12:40.093 align:middle line:90%
if they have confidence.

00:12:40.093 --> 00:12:41.495 align:middle line:84%
Now, a lot of them don't
have the confidence,

00:12:41.495 --> 00:12:43.129 align:middle line:84%
they don't have the
training, and so they go

00:12:43.129 --> 00:12:44.598 align:middle line:90%
over to their emotional side,

00:12:44.598 --> 00:12:46.366 align:middle line:84%
where they're not going
to be as productive.

00:12:46.366 --> 00:12:48.401 align:middle line:84%
For women their first
reaction is supposed

00:12:48.401 --> 00:12:50.937 align:middle line:84%
to be emotional to
small stresses.

00:12:50.937 --> 00:12:53.139 align:middle line:84%
So when a woman is having
an emotional reaction

00:12:53.139 --> 00:12:55.742 align:middle line:84%
to a small stress, out of
frustration, or disappointment,

00:12:55.742 --> 00:12:58.311 align:middle line:84%
or a concern, "But wait, we
can't do that because of this,"

00:12:58.311 --> 00:13:01.147 align:middle line:84%
and a guy goes, "Why is she
getting so emotional about this?

00:13:01.147 --> 00:13:02.616 align:middle line:90%
Can't she handle this?"

00:13:02.616 --> 00:13:05.452 align:middle line:84%
Because if a man gets
emotional about little problems,

00:13:05.452 --> 00:13:07.454 align:middle line:84%
it's a sign he really
can't handle it.

00:13:07.454 --> 00:13:10.457 align:middle line:84%
So it's a symptom of
incompetence on Mars

00:13:10.457 --> 00:13:13.493 align:middle line:84%
so men are taught to not show
emotions in the workplace.

00:13:13.493 --> 00:13:15.829 align:middle line:84%
But for women this is a
female value coming in.

00:13:15.829 --> 00:13:19.099 align:middle line:84%
Emotions are really powerful
because they help women to cope

00:13:19.099 --> 00:13:22.102 align:middle line:84%
with stress and they always have
some wisdom, because they point

00:13:22.102 --> 00:13:24.804 align:middle line:84%
out how we have to
adjust our expectations.

00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:26.439 align:middle line:90%
They help us to become flexible.

00:13:26.439 --> 00:13:28.475 align:middle line:84%
They help us to see
things differently.

00:13:28.475 --> 00:13:30.477 align:middle line:84%
And she always has a
different perspective.

00:13:30.477 --> 00:13:33.680 align:middle line:84%
It's amazing if we can just
open our minds and our hearts

00:13:33.680 --> 00:13:35.882 align:middle line:90%
to valuing what women bring in.

00:13:35.882 --> 00:13:38.351 align:middle line:84%
But men don't know
what men don't know.

00:13:38.351 --> 00:13:40.053 align:middle line:84%
That's the -- they think
they already know it all,

00:13:40.053 --> 00:13:42.822 align:middle line:84%
and they have no idea of
these gender differences

00:13:42.822 --> 00:13:44.124 align:middle line:90%
and these blind spots.

00:13:44.124 --> 00:13:46.960 align:middle line:84%
And I noticed the other day
I was in a hurry driving,

00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:50.330 align:middle line:84%
and I realized that when
you're going really fast,

00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:53.099 align:middle line:84%
it's even more important to
realize there's blind spots

00:13:53.099 --> 00:13:56.102 align:middle line:84%
in your car, because you
can shift lanes very quickly

00:13:56.102 --> 00:13:57.704 align:middle line:90%
and run right into somebody.

00:13:57.704 --> 00:13:58.872 align:middle line:90%
And what's happening right now

00:13:58.872 --> 00:14:04.177 align:middle line:84%
in a historical perspective
is an accelerated,

00:14:04.177 --> 00:14:07.380 align:middle line:84%
fast transformation never
before in history have men

00:14:07.380 --> 00:14:11.117 align:middle line:84%
and women worked hand-in-hand,
side-by-side in the work world

00:14:11.117 --> 00:14:14.154 align:middle line:84%
and then participating
equally in the home life.

00:14:14.154 --> 00:14:16.189 align:middle line:84%
This is just not the
history of this planet.

00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:19.759 align:middle line:84%
This is a huge shift and it's
accelerated very, very quickly

00:14:19.759 --> 00:14:21.895 align:middle line:84%
so it's even more important
that we become aware

00:14:21.895 --> 00:14:24.331 align:middle line:90%
of our own blind spots.

00:14:24.331 --> 00:14:27.233 align:middle line:84%
For men we tend to be
oblivious of who women are,

00:14:27.233 --> 00:14:28.969 align:middle line:84%
what they need, what
they can offer,

00:14:28.969 --> 00:14:31.037 align:middle line:84%
and how they communicate
differently.

00:14:31.037 --> 00:14:33.573 align:middle line:84%
For women they tend
to be oblivious

00:14:33.573 --> 00:14:37.510 align:middle line:84%
that men are not
intending to exclude them,

00:14:37.510 --> 00:14:40.914 align:middle line:84%
that men are not
appreciating them purposefully.

00:14:40.914 --> 00:14:42.648 align:middle line:84%
You know, there was
a time, and still is

00:14:42.648 --> 00:14:45.919 align:middle line:90%
to some extent, rampant sexism.

00:14:45.919 --> 00:14:48.221 align:middle line:84%
But today there's
an openness in men,

00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:49.756 align:middle line:90%
they just need the education.

00:14:49.756 --> 00:14:52.826 align:middle line:84%
So in one study at Harvard
showed that if somebody steps

00:14:52.826 --> 00:14:56.162 align:middle line:84%
on your foot, your stress levels
go up a little and they go down.

00:14:56.162 --> 00:14:58.198 align:middle line:84%
But if somebody steps
on your foot

00:14:58.198 --> 00:15:02.102 align:middle line:84%
and you feel it was intentional,
then you've got days of mulling

00:15:02.102 --> 00:15:04.704 align:middle line:84%
over and thinking about it, and
it carries over into everything

00:15:04.704 --> 00:15:06.172 align:middle line:90%
and it gradually builds up.

00:15:06.172 --> 00:15:07.574 align:middle line:90%
So that's sort of the benefit.

00:15:07.574 --> 00:15:09.542 align:middle line:84%
For women can learn
for themselves,

00:15:09.542 --> 00:15:11.111 align:middle line:90%
men can learn for themselves.

00:15:11.111 --> 00:15:13.680 align:middle line:84%
But as females, as women
understand their husbands

00:15:13.680 --> 00:15:16.016 align:middle line:84%
better, their workplace
better, then they have --

00:15:16.016 --> 00:15:18.952 align:middle line:84%
they learn a new way to
communicate with men.

00:15:18.952 --> 00:15:20.787 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's a lot of
women today who have gotten

00:15:20.787 --> 00:15:23.723 align:middle line:84%
in very top places because
they could think like men.

00:15:23.723 --> 00:15:25.191 align:middle line:84%
They understand the
way men think,

00:15:25.191 --> 00:15:27.260 align:middle line:84%
they understand how
to motivate a man.

00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:29.162 align:middle line:84%
If you confront men
with negativity,

00:15:29.162 --> 00:15:31.531 align:middle line:90%
or complaint, he just turns off.

00:15:31.531 --> 00:15:34.234 align:middle line:84%
But learning how to ask for
what you want, learning how

00:15:34.234 --> 00:15:37.570 align:middle line:84%
to give feedback in a way that's
flattering, as opposed to --

00:15:37.570 --> 00:15:39.806 align:middle line:84%
well instead of saying,
"I don't understand that,"

00:15:39.806 --> 00:15:40.874 align:middle line:90%
say something like, "Well,

00:15:40.874 --> 00:15:42.208 align:middle line:84%
that's something I
haven't thought about.

00:15:42.208 --> 00:15:44.110 align:middle line:84%
Help me to understand
that better."

00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:47.614 align:middle line:84%
And then also saying something
like, "That makes sense."

00:15:47.614 --> 00:15:49.182 align:middle line:84%
But I have another
way of looking at it,

00:15:49.182 --> 00:15:51.518 align:middle line:84%
but first acknowledge
what you've heard.

00:15:51.518 --> 00:15:53.987 align:middle line:84%
Instead of feeling like
you're with an enemy,

00:15:53.987 --> 00:15:56.122 align:middle line:84%
you're with someone
who really truly wants

00:15:56.122 --> 00:15:57.323 align:middle line:90%
to support you as well.

00:15:57.323 --> 00:15:59.492 align:middle line:84%
And there's this win-win
awareness that we have

00:15:59.492 --> 00:16:01.061 align:middle line:84%
to bring more into
the workplace,

00:16:01.061 --> 00:16:03.963 align:middle line:84%
both on the female side
and on the male side.

00:16:03.963 --> 00:16:06.599 align:middle line:84%
But what I help women to
understand over and over,

00:16:06.599 --> 00:16:08.701 align:middle line:84%
there's so much potential
you can get out of men

00:16:08.701 --> 00:16:10.937 align:middle line:84%
if you just know
how to talk to them.

00:16:10.937 --> 00:16:14.074 align:middle line:84%
>> L: [Laughs] We hear
lots of the men --

00:16:14.074 --> 00:16:16.843 align:middle line:84%
you know, this balance
needs to happen in all of us

00:16:16.843 --> 00:16:20.346 align:middle line:84%
between the masculine and the
feminine energy inside of us.

00:16:20.346 --> 00:16:24.150 align:middle line:84%
But is that really --
you're not really saying yes

00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:25.318 align:middle line:90%
to that, are you?

00:16:25.318 --> 00:16:27.087 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: Well, I'm saying
yes and I'm saying no,

00:16:27.087 --> 00:16:28.788 align:middle line:84%
because I'm like the
forerunner of all this.

00:16:28.788 --> 00:16:31.758 align:middle line:84%
You know, 30 years ago I
was like pure feminist,

00:16:31.758 --> 00:16:33.393 align:middle line:84%
"Let's make men all
into good wives."

00:16:33.393 --> 00:16:35.328 align:middle line:84%
[Laughs] Because that's what
the women wanted, you know,

00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:36.496 align:middle line:90%
"I wanted to be in his heart.

00:16:36.496 --> 00:16:37.730 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to share his feelings.

00:16:37.730 --> 00:16:39.499 align:middle line:84%
I wanted him to talk
about his day."

00:16:39.499 --> 00:16:41.901 align:middle line:84%
So I taught men how to do that
and the women wanted a divorce,

00:16:41.901 --> 00:16:43.002 align:middle line:90%
women were not turned on,

00:16:43.002 --> 00:16:44.838 align:middle line:84%
because he becomes
like a girlfriend.

00:16:44.838 --> 00:16:45.972 align:middle line:90%
>> L: Yes.

00:16:45.972 --> 00:16:47.307 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: You know, they
want him to be a man,

00:16:47.307 --> 00:16:48.808 align:middle line:84%
but then they also want him
to have some sensitivities.

00:16:48.808 --> 00:16:51.444 align:middle line:84%
When a woman is saying, you
know, "I want you to open up,"

00:16:51.444 --> 00:16:54.147 align:middle line:84%
really what she's saying
is, "I want you to hear me."

00:16:54.147 --> 00:16:56.616 align:middle line:84%
But often when women want to be
heard the first thing they say

00:16:56.616 --> 00:16:58.885 align:middle line:84%
to a man is, "Tell
me about your day."

00:16:58.885 --> 00:17:01.221 align:middle line:84%
When really what a woman can
do is say, "Hey, you don't have

00:17:01.221 --> 00:17:02.755 align:middle line:84%
to say anything if
you don't want to,

00:17:02.755 --> 00:17:04.290 align:middle line:90%
I just need your attention.

00:17:04.290 --> 00:17:07.494 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to tell you about my
day, and you just have to listen

00:17:07.494 --> 00:17:09.995 align:middle line:84%
and I'll feel better and give
you a big hug afterwards.

00:17:09.995 --> 00:17:12.031 align:middle line:84%
And I'd prefer if
you say nothing."

00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:14.801 align:middle line:84%
You see, this is like something
a woman would never think of,

00:17:14.801 --> 00:17:17.137 align:middle line:84%
because if you said that to
a girlfriend she'd hate you.

00:17:17.137 --> 00:17:19.839 align:middle line:84%
"What do you mean, this is
a one-sided conversation?"

00:17:19.839 --> 00:17:22.876 align:middle line:84%
And many women when I teach this
in the beginning they will say,

00:17:22.876 --> 00:17:24.077 align:middle line:90%
"Well, that's not what I want.

00:17:24.077 --> 00:17:26.079 align:middle line:84%
I want a sharing back
and forth," and so forth.

00:17:26.079 --> 00:17:27.947 align:middle line:84%
They have these ideas
of what it looks

