00:25:19.252 --> 00:25:22.254 align:middle line:84%
" she said it in the nicest
tone of voice, asking is --

00:25:22.254 --> 00:25:24.290 align:middle line:90%
it's an art how to ask.

00:25:24.290 --> 00:25:25.992 align:middle line:84%
She said, "Oh, John
-- " I was --

00:25:25.992 --> 00:25:27.727 align:middle line:84%
we happened to be in the
same part of the room,

00:25:27.727 --> 00:25:30.529 align:middle line:84%
"would you put your
t-shirts in the hamper?"

00:25:30.529 --> 00:25:31.697 align:middle line:90%
I said, "Sure."

00:25:31.697 --> 00:25:33.666 align:middle line:84%
She had no issue about
it, "You forgot again.

00:25:33.666 --> 00:25:34.600 align:middle line:90%
That's 3 t-shirts.

00:25:34.600 --> 00:25:35.401 align:middle line:90%
How could you wait?"

00:25:35.401 --> 00:25:37.003 align:middle line:90%
She said, "Oh, you're here.

00:25:37.003 --> 00:25:39.005 align:middle line:84%
Oh, would you put your 3
t-shirts in the hamper?"

00:25:39.005 --> 00:25:40.139 align:middle line:90%
I said, "Sure."

00:25:40.139 --> 00:25:41.474 align:middle line:90%
I put it in the hamper.

00:25:41.474 --> 00:25:42.942 align:middle line:84%
And I still remember
the response.

00:25:42.942 --> 00:25:44.744 align:middle line:90%
This is 24 years ago.

00:25:44.744 --> 00:25:48.014 align:middle line:84%
She takes a deep
breath and relaxes,

00:25:48.014 --> 00:25:50.716 align:middle line:84%
"Look how beautiful
the room looks now."

00:25:50.716 --> 00:25:52.051 align:middle line:90%
And this was my experience.

00:25:52.051 --> 00:25:53.185 align:middle line:90%
Men are oblivious.

00:25:53.185 --> 00:25:55.054 align:middle line:84%
I looked around and
I said, "Yes.

00:25:55.054 --> 00:25:56.355 align:middle line:90%
I did that."

00:25:56.355 --> 00:25:58.457 align:middle line:84%
So now I own -- of
course she did all of it,

00:25:58.457 --> 00:26:01.994 align:middle line:84%
I just put my t-shirts away,
but I owned it as success.

00:26:01.994 --> 00:26:05.431 align:middle line:84%
Men remember those things
that create success.

00:26:05.431 --> 00:26:07.333 align:middle line:90%
And when they forget even that,

00:26:07.333 --> 00:26:08.934 align:middle line:84%
they'll always forget
some things,

00:26:08.934 --> 00:26:11.637 align:middle line:84%
you ask again as
if the first time.

00:26:11.637 --> 00:26:12.838 align:middle line:90%
This is the training.

00:26:12.838 --> 00:26:14.540 align:middle line:84%
Most women when they ask
the second or third time,

00:26:14.540 --> 00:26:15.775 align:middle line:90%
they're so mad at you.

00:26:15.775 --> 00:26:18.110 align:middle line:84%
And most women have given
up asking and they walk

00:26:18.110 --> 00:26:19.812 align:middle line:84%
around going, "I have
to do it all myself.

00:26:19.812 --> 00:26:21.347 align:middle line:90%
I have to do it all myself."

00:26:21.347 --> 00:26:22.748 align:middle line:90%
Then they feel resentment.

00:26:22.748 --> 00:26:25.918 align:middle line:84%
And anytime you ask a man to do
something with a tone of voice

00:26:25.918 --> 00:26:29.155 align:middle line:84%
of resentment, you will create
a resistance in him rather

00:26:29.155 --> 00:26:32.425 align:middle line:84%
than a memory and a desire
to please and support.

00:26:32.425 --> 00:26:34.627 align:middle line:84%
And yes, does that mean
he doesn't love you

00:26:34.627 --> 00:26:36.395 align:middle line:84%
if he doesn't desire to
support, it means he's

00:26:36.395 --> 00:26:37.730 align:middle line:90%
in his defensive mode.

00:26:37.730 --> 00:26:41.834 align:middle line:84%
We all get in defensive modes,
not just men, also women.

00:26:41.834 --> 00:26:43.202 align:middle line:84%
And when you're in
that defensive mode,

00:26:43.202 --> 00:26:46.038 align:middle line:84%
we get kind of stubborn
and passive-aggressive,

00:26:46.038 --> 00:26:47.740 align:middle line:90%
and -- or we just forget.

00:26:47.740 --> 00:26:51.577 align:middle line:84%
So the art is to constantly open
the door to invite him through,

00:26:51.577 --> 00:26:54.680 align:middle line:84%
if you're a woman, and
for a man the art is

00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:57.116 align:middle line:84%
to consistently understand
the little things

00:26:57.116 --> 00:26:59.418 align:middle line:84%
that make women happy
and continue to persist,

00:26:59.418 --> 00:27:02.088 align:middle line:84%
and leaning in and
providing these little things

00:27:02.088 --> 00:27:04.523 align:middle line:90%
that make the big difference.

00:27:04.523 --> 00:27:05.758 align:middle line:90%
>> L: Yes.

00:27:05.758 --> 00:27:07.626 align:middle line:84%
Last advice for people that
are into a relationship

00:27:07.626 --> 00:27:12.298 align:middle line:84%
that is just not good for
them, there is really some big,

00:27:12.298 --> 00:27:13.899 align:middle line:90%
big challenges in there.

00:27:13.899 --> 00:27:16.836 align:middle line:84%
How do we get out
of a relationship

00:27:16.836 --> 00:27:19.071 align:middle line:90%
that just no longer works,

00:27:19.071 --> 00:27:22.074 align:middle line:84%
and where the other person
would be manipulative,

00:27:22.074 --> 00:27:25.411 align:middle line:90%
or just really hold us back?

00:27:25.411 --> 00:27:26.946 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: To get out
of a relationship

00:27:26.946 --> 00:27:30.416 align:middle line:84%
that really shouldn't happen;
certain concepts I deal with,

00:27:30.416 --> 00:27:35.821 align:middle line:84%
and the first step is what I
suggest to people is find a book

00:27:35.821 --> 00:27:37.990 align:middle line:84%
and that helps describe
your relationship

00:27:37.990 --> 00:27:40.292 align:middle line:84%
so you can see how
you're contributing

00:27:40.292 --> 00:27:42.261 align:middle line:84%
or not contributing
to the problem.

00:27:42.261 --> 00:27:43.629 align:middle line:84%
Because the first
thing I see is --

00:27:43.629 --> 00:27:46.532 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I've seen thousands of
couples and they always come

00:27:46.532 --> 00:27:48.801 align:middle line:84%
in -- I'm kind of like the
last exit before divorce,

00:27:48.801 --> 00:27:51.337 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes they've got
the papers in their hand.

00:27:51.337 --> 00:27:52.972 align:middle line:84%
And I always let
the partner know

00:27:52.972 --> 00:27:55.608 align:middle line:84%
who wants the divorce
most I point

00:27:55.608 --> 00:27:58.677 align:middle line:84%
out to them how they're
responsible for the problem.

00:27:58.677 --> 00:28:01.814 align:middle line:84%
Most people do not see they're
responsible for the problem.

00:28:01.814 --> 00:28:04.049 align:middle line:84%
Most people feel they're in
a dysfunctional relationship

00:28:04.049 --> 00:28:05.718 align:middle line:84%
and they have nothing
to do with it.

00:28:05.718 --> 00:28:06.485 align:middle line:90%
"That's not my fault.

00:28:06.485 --> 00:28:07.520 align:middle line:90%
I'm not doing it."

00:28:07.520 --> 00:28:09.622 align:middle line:84%
They don't see how
they contribute.

00:28:09.622 --> 00:28:13.025 align:middle line:84%
And not that every
couple I help --

00:28:13.025 --> 00:28:14.560 align:middle line:84%
sometimes it's best
they get a divorce,

00:28:14.560 --> 00:28:17.863 align:middle line:84%
and that's when a person's not
mature enough to make changes.

00:28:17.863 --> 00:28:20.299 align:middle line:84%
But with changes often people
really don't have a choice

00:28:20.299 --> 00:28:22.134 align:middle line:84%
because nobody's
giving them an option,

00:28:22.134 --> 00:28:23.903 align:middle line:90%
like people who have addictions.

00:28:23.903 --> 00:28:25.571 align:middle line:84%
You know, and I always
tell couples,

00:28:25.571 --> 00:28:27.673 align:middle line:84%
"If your partner's having an
addiction, they need to go

00:28:27.673 --> 00:28:28.774 align:middle line:90%
to get addiction help.

00:28:28.774 --> 00:28:30.476 align:middle line:84%
That's not something
you can do, and you need

00:28:30.476 --> 00:28:32.211 align:middle line:90%
to set a boundary for that."

00:28:32.211 --> 00:28:34.446 align:middle line:84%
So learning to set those
boundaries is really important.

00:28:34.446 --> 00:28:37.049 align:middle line:84%
And often you need the
support of other people.

00:28:37.049 --> 00:28:38.918 align:middle line:84%
You need somebody to
help you to do that.

00:28:38.918 --> 00:28:41.287 align:middle line:84%
But in my experience
most people who feel

00:28:41.287 --> 00:28:43.255 align:middle line:84%
like their problem
is dysfunctional,

00:28:43.255 --> 00:28:45.224 align:middle line:84%
they don't understand
how they created a

00:28:45.224 --> 00:28:46.992 align:middle line:90%
dysfunctional relationship.

00:28:46.992 --> 00:28:49.028 align:middle line:84%
Because really what it takes
is a lot of little things

00:28:49.028 --> 00:28:52.097 align:middle line:84%
that build up until you have
irreconcilable differences

00:28:52.097 --> 00:28:53.766 align:middle line:90%
and bad behavior.

00:28:53.766 --> 00:28:56.068 align:middle line:84%
For example, if women
could understand, you know,

00:28:56.068 --> 00:28:58.204 align:middle line:84%
what I'm doing counseling
for couples

00:28:58.204 --> 00:28:59.638 align:middle line:84%
where one's been
violent or something.

00:28:59.638 --> 00:29:01.907 align:middle line:84%
It's not always the man,
sometimes the woman.

00:29:01.907 --> 00:29:05.444 align:middle line:84%
So but I let them see that yes,
you're a victim of violence,

00:29:05.444 --> 00:29:07.213 align:middle line:90%
but you contributed to it.

00:29:07.213 --> 00:29:09.548 align:middle line:84%
And it's a hard thing to
point out to somebody because,

00:29:09.548 --> 00:29:10.916 align:middle line:84%
"Then does that mean
it's my fault?"

00:29:10.916 --> 00:29:12.151 align:middle line:90%
"No; it's not your fault.

00:29:12.151 --> 00:29:14.353 align:middle line:84%
If a person is violent, they
should never be violent.

00:29:14.353 --> 00:29:17.389 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing you do that
justifies their violence.

00:29:17.389 --> 00:29:20.459 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time if you
behave in a certain way,

00:29:20.459 --> 00:29:22.328 align:middle line:84%
you bring out the
worst of your partner."

00:29:22.328 --> 00:29:25.264 align:middle line:84%
And the great news there is
if you see how you behave

00:29:25.264 --> 00:29:27.833 align:middle line:84%
or interact to bring out
the worst in someone,

00:29:27.833 --> 00:29:30.502 align:middle line:84%
then you can realize that
if I shift that behavior,

00:29:30.502 --> 00:29:32.538 align:middle line:84%
I can bring out the
best in them.

00:29:32.538 --> 00:29:34.607 align:middle line:84%
So, you know, that's -- I
don't readily push people

00:29:34.607 --> 00:29:37.476 align:middle line:84%
into divorce, but the clear
thing is when you are there,

00:29:37.476 --> 00:29:39.245 align:middle line:84%
make sure that you have the
support of other people,

00:29:39.245 --> 00:29:40.880 align:middle line:90%
otherwise you tend to go back.

00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:43.315 align:middle line:84%
>> L: How about for
this manipulative mind

00:29:43.315 --> 00:29:46.752 align:middle line:84%
or if we feel we're with
somebody that is manipulative

00:29:46.752 --> 00:29:49.855 align:middle line:84%
and that we have done some
things that we shouldn't have;

00:29:49.855 --> 00:29:53.058 align:middle line:84%
because I feel like we should
have enough self-respect too

00:29:53.058 --> 00:29:54.193 align:middle line:90%
to accept or not, right,

00:29:54.193 --> 00:29:55.961 align:middle line:84%
so we create this
reality in this couple.

00:29:55.961 --> 00:29:58.063 align:middle line:84%
>> JG: By not having a
boundary; you create a reality

00:29:58.063 --> 00:29:59.465 align:middle line:84%
by not being able
to set a boundary.

00:29:59.465 --> 00:30:00.799 align:middle line:84%
Here is the irony of
what you're saying.

00:30:00.799 --> 00:30:04.370 align:middle line:84%
When I do my weekend workshops,
I have the men and women

00:30:04.370 --> 00:30:06.505 align:middle line:84%
in different rooms, and we
list out all the complaints.

00:30:06.505 --> 00:30:10.276 align:middle line:84%
The number top 3 for men and
top 3 for women when we get it

00:30:10.276 --> 00:30:13.913 align:middle line:84%
down to each group is, "My
partner's too controlling."

00:30:13.913 --> 00:30:16.348 align:middle line:84%
There's always controlling
men and controlling women.

00:30:16.348 --> 00:30:17.816 align:middle line:84%
And when you have a
controlling partner,

00:30:17.816 --> 00:30:19.685 align:middle line:84%
usually you're the person
who doesn't know how

00:30:19.685 --> 00:30:21.987 align:middle line:84%
to set boundaries or
ask for what you want.

00:30:21.987 --> 00:30:24.256 align:middle line:84%
And be tough, but
in a loving way.

00:30:24.256 --> 00:30:26.058 align:middle line:84%
You can be tough
in a loving way.

00:30:26.058 --> 00:30:27.393 align:middle line:90%
Just because somebody walks

00:30:27.393 --> 00:30:29.895 align:middle line:84%
over your boundaries
doesn't mean they can't learn

00:30:29.895 --> 00:30:31.964 align:middle line:84%
to set a boundary -- I mean,
to respect your boundary.

00:30:31.964 --> 00:30:35.334 align:middle line:84%
You have to first respect
yourself and learn how to do it

00:30:35.334 --> 00:30:37.169 align:middle line:84%
so you feel like
I'm a good person

00:30:37.169 --> 00:30:39.338 align:middle line:90%
at the same time I'm saying no.

00:30:39.338 --> 00:30:41.073 align:middle line:90%
And that's a challenge to that.

00:30:41.073 --> 00:30:43.409 align:middle line:84%
Here's a little example of how
I did it in my relationship.

00:30:43.409 --> 00:30:46.145 align:middle line:84%
One of the aspects I teach
about men and women is

00:30:46.145 --> 00:30:48.013 align:middle line:90%
that we have a need for space.

00:30:48.013 --> 00:30:51.050 align:middle line:84%
Men tend to feel a greater
need for space, distance,

00:30:51.050 --> 00:30:52.384 align:middle line:90%
because it's only in distance

00:30:52.384 --> 00:30:54.420 align:middle line:84%
that we rebuild our
testosterone.

00:30:54.420 --> 00:30:57.222 align:middle line:84%
And men need to rebuild a lot
more testosterone than women

00:30:57.222 --> 00:30:58.857 align:middle line:90%
to be happy and healthy.

00:30:58.857 --> 00:31:00.392 align:middle line:84%
So I had spent the whole
weekend with Bonnie.

00:31:00.392 --> 00:31:02.528 align:middle line:84%
We were helping move her
aunt up to where we lived

00:31:02.528 --> 00:31:05.731 align:middle line:84%
in Northern California to help
her because she was getting old.

00:31:05.731 --> 00:31:07.766 align:middle line:84%
And we spent like 4 days
packing up her place

00:31:07.766 --> 00:31:09.335 align:middle line:84%
and doing the whole
thing together.

00:31:09.335 --> 00:31:12.171 align:middle line:84%
And when we got back up
exhausted and tired I said

00:31:12.171 --> 00:31:14.807 align:middle line:84%
to my wife, "I'm going to go
out with the guys tonight."

00:31:14.807 --> 00:31:17.176 align:middle line:84%
And she went, "Oh, but we
haven't had any time together."

00:31:17.176 --> 00:31:18.978 align:middle line:84%
Now, I was able to
translate that into,

00:31:18.978 --> 00:31:21.280 align:middle line:84%
"We haven't had any
quality time together."

00:31:21.280 --> 00:31:23.015 align:middle line:84%
But I knew I couldn't
give her quality time.

00:31:23.015 --> 00:31:27.219 align:middle line:84%
I needed to take time away from
all that to be with my buddies,

00:31:27.219 --> 00:31:29.221 align:middle line:84%
and I said to her, "I
just needed time to be

00:31:29.221 --> 00:31:30.089 align:middle line:90%
with my friend tonight.

00:31:30.089 --> 00:31:31.390 align:middle line:90%
We're going to go to the movies.

00:31:31.390 --> 00:31:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And tomorrow I'm going to
do something very special.

00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:36.628 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to plan a dinner,
we're going to go out on a date

00:31:36.628 --> 00:31:38.197 align:middle line:84%
and I'll surprise
you what it is."

00:31:38.197 --> 00:31:39.865 align:middle line:90%
And she was not happy with that.

00:31:39.865 --> 00:31:41.967 align:middle line:84%
She looked at me with
great disapproval.

00:31:41.967 --> 00:31:43.502 align:middle line:90%
And I had to stand my ground

00:31:43.502 --> 00:31:46.405 align:middle line:84%
and also assure her
everything was going to be okay.

00:31:46.405 --> 00:31:48.574 align:middle line:84%
If I was one of these wimpy
guys who don't understand

00:31:48.574 --> 00:31:50.476 align:middle line:84%
that you have to take care
of your own self as well

00:31:50.476 --> 00:31:53.145 align:middle line:84%
as your partner -- it's a
balance, he would have looked

00:31:53.145 --> 00:31:55.414 align:middle line:84%
at those disapproving
eyes and said, "Okay.

00:31:55.414 --> 00:31:56.815 align:middle line:90%
I'll stay home tonight."

00:31:56.815 --> 00:31:59.084 align:middle line:84%
And I knew if I said I'd stay
home tonight there wouldn't be

00:31:59.084 --> 00:32:00.919 align:middle line:84%
any quality intimacy
because I needed

00:32:00.919 --> 00:32:03.956 align:middle line:84%
to find myself again
as a separate entity.

00:32:03.956 --> 00:32:05.958 align:middle line:84%
And maybe some women are
saying, "Well, what about her?

00:32:05.958 --> 00:32:09.161 align:middle line:84%
She also needs to find
herself as a separate entity."

00:32:09.161 --> 00:32:11.997 align:middle line:84%
And usually it's the women
who tend to have the wisdom

00:32:11.997 --> 00:32:13.966 align:middle line:84%
of how much time we
should spend together,

00:32:13.966 --> 00:32:15.067 align:middle line:90%
and men have the wisdom

00:32:15.067 --> 00:32:16.902 align:middle line:84%
of saying we should
have some time apart.

00:32:16.902 --> 00:32:20.372 align:middle line:84%
So oxytocin, the hormone
that lowers stress for women,

00:32:20.372 --> 00:32:23.575 align:middle line:84%
is the hormonal bonding, and
togetherness, and sharing.

00:32:23.575 --> 00:32:26.779 align:middle line:84%
Testosterone is what creates
passion, but it's distance.

00:32:26.779 --> 00:32:30.049 align:middle line:84%
I mean, think about like even
in sex, you know, when I'm away

00:32:30.049 --> 00:32:32.518 align:middle line:84%
for a while, boy, the
sex is so much better

00:32:32.518 --> 00:32:35.721 align:middle line:84%
because I've had a chance
to rebuild my testosterone.

00:32:35.721 --> 00:32:37.689 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, with all
this great information

00:32:37.689 --> 00:32:39.758 align:middle line:84%
about psychology that I've
helped so many couples

00:32:39.758 --> 00:32:43.195 align:middle line:84%
in the world with, now for the
last 10 years I've been focusing

00:32:43.195 --> 00:32:47.066 align:middle line:84%
on, "And you have to take
into consideration the body,"

00:32:47.066 --> 00:32:48.867 align:middle line:84%
because you could be doing
all the right things,

00:32:48.867 --> 00:32:52.171 align:middle line:84%
but because the food we
eat today is nutritionally

00:32:52.171 --> 00:32:55.908 align:middle line:84%
deficient, because the
pesticides affect the body

00:32:55.908 --> 00:32:59.144 align:middle line:84%
like estrogen, soy
could affect the body

00:32:59.144 --> 00:33:01.580 align:middle line:84%
and suppress the
testosterone levels in men,

00:33:01.580 --> 00:33:04.450 align:middle line:84%
a lot of different things that
we're being exposed to now

00:33:04.450 --> 00:33:06.552 align:middle line:84%
that historically we've
never been exposed to,

00:33:06.552 --> 00:33:08.454 align:middle line:90%
are messing with our hormones.

00:33:08.454 --> 00:33:10.989 align:middle line:84%
And for some women the easy
answer symptomatic relief is,

00:33:10.989 --> 00:33:13.559 align:middle line:84%
"Go get hormones," which
sometimes is very helpful,

00:33:13.559 --> 00:33:15.494 align:middle line:84%
but you're not treating
the cause.

00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:18.864 align:middle line:84%
We want to get back to how to
actually create healthy hormones

00:33:18.864 --> 00:33:21.233 align:middle line:84%
and understand that by
looking at our diet,

00:33:21.233 --> 00:33:23.068 align:middle line:84%
looking at our exercise,
for women,

00:33:23.068 --> 00:33:25.771 align:middle line:84%
making sure that you're
doing like yoga classes.

00:33:25.771 --> 00:33:27.606 align:middle line:84%
It's so -- like that's
a great thing.

00:33:27.606 --> 00:33:30.209 align:middle line:84%
